body:
 For your question in general, I think the answer is yes. MPI is good in bandwidth but bad in latency, so it is suitable for blob data transmission which frequently happens in data parallelism.

You could use MPI to start parameter server and worker instance (your mxnet program) like [here](https://github.com/dmlc/ps-lite/blob/master/tracker/dmlc_mpi.py). But the underlying communication is not based on MPI.

@mli do you have any comments?
